<DESC>The U.S. Department of Agriculture, Agricultural Research Service intends to make a sole source procurement to SAPIDYNE INSTRUMENTS located at 700 W. Diamond St., Boise, ID 83705 for the upgrade of an existing KinExA Model #3100 series to a Model #3200 series.
<p>The upgrade includes the following:<br />1. Upgrade of existing KinExA 3000/3100 to 3200. A one-year warranty on upgraded parts.<br />2. KinExA Autosampler - made exclusively for use with the KinExA 3200 Instrument. Includes a one-year warranty, training and installation.</p>
<p>The government has determined that Sapidyne Instruments is the manufacturer of the model owned by the government and is so for the upgrade, warranties and training. Pursuant to FAR 6.302-1, Only One Responsible Source and No Other Supplies or Services Will Satisfy Agency Requirements, the government intends to award a firm, fixed-price purchase order to Sapidyne Instruments without competition on or about June 1, 2018. These products will be delivered to the USDA-ARS-PWA Foodborne Toxin Detection and Prevention Research Unit, 800 Buchanan 